## 5. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [Security Officer / CISO] | Owns the register; verifies BAA-before-PHI; flags stale assurance and overdue reviews. |
| [Privacy Officer] | Confirms BAA Required determinations and BAA terms (with counsel). |
| [Procurement / Vendor Owner] | Initiates intake; keeps relationship rows current; drives renewals and offboarding. |
| Vendor Owners | Maintain their vendors' entries; provide assurance evidence at review. |

See `../governance/roles-and-responsibilities.md.template` for full role definitions.

## 6. Exceptions
Onboarding or continuing a vendor outside the required process (e.g., an expired BAA still in use) requires documented risk acceptance per `../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template` — except that **PHI sharing without an executed BAA is not waivable** (POL-GOV-11 §6).

## 7. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
The register is reviewed for completeness, current assurance, executed BAAs, and timely reassessment per POL-VEN-01 §11, and reported to management review (`../governance/management-review.md.template`). Assessors review it as primary evidence of the third-party risk process. A vendor breach or BAA lapse triggers `../healthcare/hipaa-breach-notification-procedure.md.template` evaluation and the incident process.

